</div><div class="post-17375 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-missiles-missile-defense tag-hypersonic tag-missiles tag-testing" id="post-17375">    
    <div class="latest-posts-post">
                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/ctracy/the-latest-us-test-flight-of-a-hypersonic-weapon-the-common-hypersonic-glide-body" class="post_thumbnail ">
            <span><img src='https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body.jpg' /></span>
        </a>

        <div class="post_details_inner">
            <h1>
                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/ctracy/the-latest-us-test-flight-of-a-hypersonic-weapon-the-common-hypersonic-glide-body" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to The Latest US Test Flight of a Hypersonic Weapon: the Common Hypersonic Glide Body">
                The Latest US Test Flight of a Hypersonic Weapon: the Common Hypersonic Glide Body                </a>
            </h1>
                            <div class="username">
                    <span class="ctracy">
                                                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/author/ctracy" title="Posts by Cameron Tracy" rel="author">Cameron Tracy</a><!--
                        -->                    </span><!--
                --></div>
                        <div class="post-date pipe">
                <p><span class="date">May 8, 2020</span> <span class="time">11:19 AM</span> EDT</p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-content">
                <div id="attachment_17389" style="max-width: 1510px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-17389" src="https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="900" srcset="https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body.jpg 1500w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body-300x180.jpg 300w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body-768x461.jpg 768w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body-1024x614.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body-183x110.jpg 183w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/hypersonic-glide-body-600x360.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A common hypersonic glide body (C-HGB) launches from Pacific Missile Range Facility during a Defense Department flight experiment, Kauai, Hawaii, March 19, 2020. Oscar Sosa/Navy.</p></div>
<p>The United States Department of Defense has been actively developing hypersonic weapons—missiles that fly through the atmosphere at more than five times the speed of sound—<a href="https://fas.org/sgp/crs/nuke/R41464.pdf">since the early 2000s</a>. <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/ctracy/the-latest-us-test-flight-of-a-hypersonic-weapon-the-common-hypersonic-glide-body" class="read-more">Read More</a></p>                                        <div class="addthis_widget"><a class="addthis_button" addthis:url="https://allthingsnuclear.org/?p=17375" addthis:title="The Latest US Test Flight of a Hypersonic Weapon: the Common Hypersonic Glide Body" href="https://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pubid=ra-4dd154a4387f0255"><img src="https://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/sm-share-en.gif" width="83" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a></div>            </div>
        </div>

        <br clear="all">
        <div class="post_details_border"></div>

    </div>

