    <div class="latest-posts-post">
                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/gkulacki/does-japan-have-nuclear-weapons" class="post_thumbnail ">
            <span><img width="183" height="110" src="https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-183x110.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-183x110.jpg 183w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-300x180.jpg 300w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-768x461.jpg 768w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-1024x614.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag-600x360.jpg 600w, https://cdn.allthingsnuclear.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/soldiers-saluting-japanese-and-american-flag.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 183px) 100vw, 183px" /></span>
        </a>

        <div class="post_details_inner">
            <h1>
                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/gkulacki/does-japan-have-nuclear-weapons" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Does Japan Have Nuclear Weapons?">
                Does Japan Have Nuclear Weapons?                </a>
            </h1>
                            <div class="username">
                    <span class="gkulacki">
                                                <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/author/gkulacki" title="Posts by Gregory Kulacki" rel="author">Gregory Kulacki</a><!--
                        --><!--
                            --><span class='mobile-hide'>,</span><span class='mobile-hide'> China project manager and senior analyst</span>
                                            </span><!--
                --></div>
                        <div class="post-date pipe">
                <p><span class="date">May 1, 2020</span> <span class="time">11:31 AM</span> EDT</p>
            </div>
            <div class="article-content">
                <p>Japan does not have its own nuclear weapons. The Japanese government considered developing them in the past, but <a href="https://www.ucsusa.org/resources/japan-and-americas-nuclear-posture" target="_blank" rel="noopener">decided</a> this would make Japan less secure. Japanese opinion polls consistently express strong public opposition to nuclear weapons. So do their elected representatives.</p>
<p>There is, however, a small group of non-elected Japanese bureaucrats with close ties to the U.S. defense establishment who <a href="http://kakujoho.net/npt/npr2018.html#akiba_e_m" target="_blank" rel="noopener">insist</a> U.S. nuclear weapons should be “the core of Japan’s security arrangements.” Wonks refer to this supposed core as “extended nuclear deterrence.” Journalists and politicians, especially in Japan, call it a “nuclear umbrella.”</p>
<p> <a href="https://allthingsnuclear.org/gkulacki/does-japan-have-nuclear-weapons" class="more-link">Read more&nbsp;&gt;</a></p>
                                        <div class="addthis_widget"><a class="addthis_button" addthis:url="https://allthingsnuclear.org/?p=17352" addthis:title="Does Japan Have Nuclear Weapons?" href="https://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pubid=ra-4dd154a4387f0255"><img src="https://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/sm-share-en.gif" width="83" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a></div>            </div>
        </div>

        <br clear="all">
        <div class="post_details_border"></div>

    </div>

